message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.NEURON - The paper deals with the problem of segmenting the left ventricular myocardium on late gadolinium enhancement cardiovascular magnetic resonance scans, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method uses chained generative adversarial networks, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The application of the method is in the medical field (cs.MED), specifically in simulating scar tissue on healthy myocardium. The paper also mentions the use of a U-Net, which is a type of neural network commonly used in medical image segmentation (cs.NEURON).
